The Creation of the World was a Vail cast upon the Face of God, with a figure
of the Godhead wrought upon this Vail, and God Himself seen through it by a dim
transparency, as the Sun in a morning, or Mist, is seen by a refracted Light
through the thick medium of earthly Vapours.
